OL,3,CCarer from Preston made to feel like
OL,4,Ccriminal after mistake on benefit form
OL,6,FGranada Reports correspondent Tim
OL,7,FScott speaks to a man who has lost
OL,8,Feverything after an error on a
OL,9,Fgovernment form.
OL,11,FA carer from Preston says an innocent
OL,12,Fmistake while filling in a benefits
OL,13,Fform led to him being made to feel
OL,14,Flike a criminal.
OL,16,FGeorge Henderson says he was taken to
OL,17,Fcourt by the Government's Department
OL,18,Ffor Work and Pensions for fraudulently
OL,19,Fclaiming benefits. He had to sell his
OL,20,Fhome to pay back nearly twenty
OL,21,Fthousand pounds
