OL,3,CCarer from Preston made to feel like
OL,4,Ccriminal after mistake on benefit form
OL,6,FGeorge says he had ticked the wrong
OL,7,Fbox on a form when he applied for
OL,8,Fcarers-allowance in 2010.
OL,10,FHe was looking after his drug-addict
OL,11,Fson who has learning difficulties. He
OL,12,Fwas also working in a local taxi
OL,13,Foffice.
OL,15,FBut his problems started when he
OL,16,Fwrongly ticked a box to say he was
OL,17,Funemployed - thinking the question
OL,18,Freferred to his son, not himself.
